UPSTREAM NOTICES
================

This software is a Swift implementation of the VOACAP (Voice of
America Coverage Analysis Program) HF propagation prediction engine,
derived from the original Fortran source code developed by the
National Telecommunications and Information Administration, Institute
for Telecommunication Sciences (NTIA/ITS), and subsequently adapted
for POSIX systems by J.A. Watson (voacapl).

The original NTIA/ITS disclaimer:

    The software contained within was developed by an agency of the
    U.S. Government. NTIA/ITS has no objection to the use of this
    software for any purpose since it is not subject to copyright
    protection in the U.S.

    No warranty, expressed or implied, is made by NTIA/ITS or the
    U.S. Government as to the accuracy, suitability and functioning
    of the program and related material, nor shall the fact of
    distribution constitute any endorsement by the U.S. Government.

The voacapl modifications by J.A. Watson are released under the
Creative Commons CC0 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication.

The VOACAP coefficient data files (itshfbc) are part of the original
NTIA/ITS distribution and are not subject to copyright protection in
the United States.
